HEADWORD: Tops-and-bottoms
<hw>Tops"-and-bot`toms</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <def>Small
rolls of dough, baked, cut in halves, and then browned in an oven, --
used as food for infants.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>'T is said that her <qex>top-and-bottoms</qex> were gilt.</q>
<rj><qau>Hood.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Top secret</ent>⟦br⟧
